nodes.bodyText:
Hi there,
I wanted to contribute to the V2 rewrite and decided to start on the Card component. I'm still a little unsure if i'm on the right track, so I got a few questions.
Am I correct to use the tailwind state classes instead of the props?
For example
// packages/core/theme/src/components/card/index.ts
isHoverable: {
  true: "hover:drop-shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition",
},
isPressable: {
  true: "cursor-pointer active:scale-95",
},

I've just seen the changes for the AvatarGroup on the feat/v2 branch. Do you expect a hook for the CardBody, CardFooter and CardHeader? Or is just adding the classes with clsx, in for example CardFooter.tsx, enough?
Example:
// packages/components/card/src/card-footer.tsx
    <Component
      ref={domRef}
      {...otherProps}
      className={clsx(
        "w-full h-auto p-3 flex items-center overflow-hidden color-inherit rounded-b-xl",
        {
          "backdrop-blur-md backdrop-saturate-[1.8]": isBlurred,
        },
        className,
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </Component>

any other guidance you can give me on how to migrate the components would be also welcome, I would love to help out on the other components!

